text: You know what's a real jump scare? Movie scenes are nothing compare to the real life experiences. I remember suddenly waking up by a feeling of a dark presence wildly directly charging at me(kind of like sleep paralysis except for some reason I can move) so I'm all shocked staring at nothing in the darkness then all of sudden a toy my nephew forgot in my house turns on and starts playing music. NOW THAT SCARED THE SHIT OUT OF ME YOU HAVE NO IDEA. The fact that I was so lost in the moment and too shocked to move and let the freaky music keep playing and in my head I'm like c'mon move and TURN IT OFF. Guess what happened after... you all think that movie can be scary? Real life experience is fucking insane, you'd be shooked for weeks and never figure it out.
